    • Method Detail

      • canAdd

        public LimitService.EvaluationResult canAdd(LocalPlayer creator,
                                            LocalWorld world,
                                            Warp.Type warpType)
        Evaluates whether the given creator can add a new Warp of the given warpType to the given world.

        This method will return a positive result if the current number of warps counted under any limit applicable for creator, world and warp type falls below the allowed maximum by at least 1.

        Parameters:
        creator - The creator who wants to add a new Warp
        world - The world the warp should be added to
        warpType - the type of the warp to add
        Returns:
        the result of the evaluation

      • canChangeType

        public LimitService.EvaluationResult canChangeType(LocalPlayer creator,
                                                   LocalWorld world,
                                                   Warp.Type oldType,
                                                   Warp.Type newType)
        Evaluates whether the given creator can change the type of an existing Warp on the given world from oldType to newType.

        This method will return a positive result if the current number of warps counted under the limit applicable for creator, world and the new warp type falls below the allowed maximum by at least 1. Any limit that counts warps from both, old and new type, is ignored.

        Parameters:
        creator - The creator of the warp
        world - The world of the warp
        oldType - the old type of the warp
        newType - the new type of the warp
        Returns:
        the result of the evaluation

      • getAssets

        public com.google.common.collect.ImmutableMap<Limit,LimitValueWarpMapping> getAssets(LocalPlayer player)
        Returns an ImmutableMap with every Limit that could affect the given player mapped to the corresponding LimitValueMapping.

        Which limit actually applies to a certain player depends on the world, the check is run for. The map returned by this method contains all limits that could apply for a player; it therefore contains all possible LimitValueMapping and can be used to display a player's assets.

        Parameters:
        player - the player
        Returns:
        a Map that mapps every limit that could affect the given player to the corresponding LimtiValueMapping
